    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Goodenia foliosa are gastrointestinal problems, such as diarrhea, due to its anti-inflammatory properties and ability to reduce gut inflammation. Goodenia foliosa has also been shown to be effective in treating respiratory issues like bronchitis, by acting as an expectorant and loosening mucus in the airways. The plant's antibacterial and antifungal properties make it an effective treatment for skin conditions like eczema, which is characterized by inflammation and irritation of the skin. Goodenia foliosa has also been used to treat fever, which is a common symptom of many illnesses, by reducing body temperature and alleviating discomfort. Additionally, the plant's diuretic properties make it a useful treatment for kidney stones, which occur when minerals and salts crystallize in the kidneys and cause pain and discomfort.",
