    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Goodenia foliosa are its anti-inflammatory activity, which is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and saponins in the plant, providing relief from pain and swelling. The analgesic and anti-pyretic properties of Goodenia foliosa, due to the bioactive compounds such as volatile oils and phenolic acids, make it effective in managing fever and reducing pain. The antimicrobial and antioxidant activities of Goodenia foliosa, resulting from the presence of flavonoids, saponins, and phenolic acids, help to protect the body from infections and oxidative stress. The antioxidant properties of Goodenia foliosa, caused by the presence of phenolic acids and flavonoids, also contribute to the prevention of cell damage and promotion of healthy aging. The anti-diarrheal and anti-emetic properties of Goodenia foliosa, due to the bioactive compounds such as volatile oils and saponins, make it useful in treating gastrointestinal disorders.",
