    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Goodenia foliosa are flavonoids, particularly kaempferol and quercetin which have been shown to possess antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. Additionally, Goodenia foliosa contains phenolic acids, such as ferulic acid and sinapic acid, which have been demonstrated to exhibit antimicrobial and antioxidant activities. The plant also contains alkaloids, including Goodenine and Goodenol, which have been reported to exhibit anti-inflammatory and antispasmodic properties. Furthermore, Goodenia foliosa contains terpenoids, particularly carotenoids and xanthophylls, which have been found to possess antioxidant and photoprotective properties. These constituents are responsible for the plant's medicinal properties, including its use in traditional medicine to treat various ailments such as fever, cough, and digestive disorders.",
