    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Goodenia foliosa are typically derived from its leaves, which are used for their medicinal properties. Infusion is a preparation made by steeping the leaves in hot water, which is then used to treat various ailments, including fever and cough. The leaves can also be made into a tea by steeping them in hot water, which is often consumed to aid in digestion and relieve respiratory issues. Tincture is another preparation made by soaking the leaves in a solvent, such as ethanol, to create a concentrated extract that can be used to treat a range of health issues. Additionally, the leaves can be made into a salve by infusing them in a carrier oil, which can be applied topically to treat skin irritations and wounds, and decoction is also made from the leaves by boiling them in water to treat gastrointestinal issues.",
