    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Goodenia foliosa improperly are gastrointestinal issues such as diarrhea and nausea, which can be attributed to its high concentration of saponins, iridoid glycosides, and phenolic compounds that can disrupt gut flora and cause adverse reactions. Skin irritation and allergic reactions may also occur due to the plant's potential to cause contact dermatitis and photoallergic reactions, particularly if the skin is exposed to direct sunlight. This is because Goodenia foliosa contains sesquiterpenes and flavonoids that can act as phototoxins, leading to inflammation and irritation. Individuals with pre-existing skin conditions or allergies should exercise caution when handling the plant, as it may exacerbate their symptoms. Furthermore, improper use of Goodenia foliosa may also lead to systemic toxicity, especially if ingested in large quantities, which can cause a range of symptoms including vomiting, abdominal pain, and respiratory distress.",
